data.title: NASW
data.meta_description: 8 Hours of video content Practice tests and sample questions with keys PowerPoint presentation from full test prep presentation ASWB and NYS exam form
data.text:
NASW-NYS is offering an eight-hour course was designed for social workers preparing to take the Masters Level ASWB exam or the Clinical Level ASWB exam.

Open to students from all states, our package was developed and presented by two of the best instructors and test prep aficionados out there. This course not only dissects the exam but will also frame the test within the foundation of social work values and give you tools for grounding yourself before, during, and after the training.

You will receive a the full recording of the training to re-watch on your own as many times as you need. Plus, the full PowerPoint presentation from the entire test prep presentation, the ASWB appointment to take exam form, the ASWB Examination Candidate Handbook, the ASWB Examination Candidate Rules Agreement, a summary of Racial and Ethnic Identity Frameworks or Models, instructions and application for disability accommodations, a database of licensing exam levels by geographic region, personal learning, style evaluation and tips, the required application form 1 for Licensure, a New York State Education Department requirement checklist with all required items hyperlinked, sample exams with exam keys, and more!

What makes our test prep different from the other options out there? The presenters.

Dr. Folusho and Dr. Kennedy are not only genuinely engaging and well versed in virtual learning, they have extensive experience real life in coaching students to reach their academic and licensure goals. Most importantly, students and past test prep attendees evaluate them with excellent marks and an overall 99.8% satisfaction rating for past presentations and recordings. Dr. Kennedy and Dr. Folusho are not here to provide easy answers, rather they truly understand biases and challenges of the exam and are committed to providing the tools to help you succeed.

This eight-hour course was designed for social workers preparing to take the Masters Level ASWB exam or the Clinical Level ASWB exam.

This course focuses on the following key areas:

1. developing necessary skills for acing standardized test,

2. reviewing concepts from the four content areas of the master level exam (Human Diversity and the Social Environment; Assessment and Intervention Planning; Interventions with Clients/Client Systems; and Professional Relationships, Values and Ethics),

3. reviewing concepts for the clinical exam (Assessment and Diagnosis; Clinical Treatments and Modalities; Psychotropic Medications; and DSM5), and
